The State Publicity Secretary of the  All Progressives Congress (APC), Segun Dipe, has confirmed the abduction of Barrister Paul Omotoso, the Ekiti State chairman of the party. Dipe in a chat with journalists said the chairman was driving in a Venza car to his country home, Imesi-Ile when the incident occurred. “The gunmen shot at one of the tyres of the car. He was taken into a Toyota Hilus van and driven off. He was alone in the car when the incident happened, according to the information we have. “It happened in the evening. We got the information at about 6 pm. The security agencies – police and Amotekun – have been alerted.